An '''acoustic membrane''' is a thin layer that [[vibrations|vibrates]] and is used in [[acoustics]] to produce or transfer [[sound]], such as a [[drum]], [[microphone]], or [[loudspeaker]].
== See also == * [[Membranophone]] * [[Vibrations of a circular membrane]]
