'''Eobacteria''' is a proposed [[clade]] characterized by [[Cavalier-Smith]].<ref name="pmid16834776">{{cite journal |author=Cavalier-Smith T |title=Rooting the tree of life by transition analyses |journal=Biol. Direct |volume=1 |issue= 1|pages=19 |year=2006 |pmid=16834776 |pmc=1586193 |doi=10.1186/1745-6150-1-19 |url=http://www.biology-direct.com/content/1//19}}</ref> Species in this group lack [[lipopolysaccharide]].<ref name="pmid20008390">{{cite journal |author=Cavalier-Smith T |title=Deep phylogeny, ancestral groups and the four ages of life |journal=Philos. Trans. R. Soc. Lond. B Biol. Sci. |volume=365 |issue=1537 |pages=111–32 |date=January 2010 |pmid=20008390 |pmc=2842702 |doi=10.1098/rstb.2009.0161 |url=http://rstb.royalsocietypublishing.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=20008390}}</ref>

The clade includes [[Hadobacteria]] and [[Chlorobacteria]].

