{{Infobox journal | italic title = force | title = Interface: a journal for and about social movements | cover = <!--to be uploaded to wiki from http://interfacejournal.nuim.ie/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/Issue-1-1.jpg--> | editor = Editorial collective | discipline = [[Sociology]], [[political sciences]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English and others | former_names = | abbreviation = | publisher = | country = | frequency = Biannually | history = 2009-present | openaccess = Yes | license = [[Creative Commons|Creative Commons "attribution non commercial no derivatives"]] | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://interfacejournal.net | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 2009-2431 | eISSN = }} '''''Interface: a journal for and about social movements''''' is an [[open access]] [[academic journal]] that covers original research and reviews of books concerned mainly with [[protest]]s, [[social movement]]s, and [[collective behavior]].
The journal has multiple editors who are responsible for different world regions and is multilingual. It was established in 2009 and appears biannually.
''Interface'' attempts to engage not only social movement scholars, but also the activists themselves.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interfacejournal.net/who-we-are/mission-statement/ |title=Mission Statement &#124; Interface: a journal for and about social movements |publisher=Interfacejournal.net |date= |accessdate=2012-09-25}}</ref>
