'''''Leptotrichia goodfellowii''''' is a [[Gram-negative]], non-[[spore]]-forming and non-motile bacterium from the genus of ''[[Leptotrichia]]'' which has been isolated from [[human blood]] of an [[endocarditis]] patient.<ref name=Leptotrichia-goodfellowii/><ref name=UniProt/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Details: DSM-19756 |journal=www.dsmz.de |url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-19756.html |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Lim |first1=YK |last2=Kweon |first2=OJ |last3=Kim |first3=HR |last4=Lee |first4=MK |title=Leptotrichia goodfellowii Infection: Case Report and Literature Review. |journal=Annals of clinical and laboratory science |date=NaN |volume=46 |issue=1 |pages=83–6 |pmid=26927348}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Liu |first1=Dongyou |title=Molecular Detection of Human Bacterial Pathogens |date=2011 |publisher=CRC Press |isbn=9781439812389 |language=en}}</ref>
